  <bookmark branch="index" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3149428"><bookmark_value>Help; index</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>Help; keywords</bookmark_value></bookmark><paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3149428" l10n="E" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="2" localize="false"/>
  <paragraph id="hd_id3153884" role="heading" level="1" oldref="5" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><variable id="00000130"><link href="text/shared/05/00000130.xhp" name="Index - Keyword Search in the Help">Index - Keyword Search in the Help</link></variable></paragraph>
  <bookmark branch="hid/SFX2_COMBOBOX_TP_HELP_INDEX_CB_INDEX" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3149662"/><paragraph l10n="U" role="paragraph" id="par_id3150960" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="3"><ahelp hid="SFX2_COMBOBOX_TP_HELP_INDEX_CB_INDEX" visibility="hidden">Double-click an entry or type the word you want to find in the index.</ahelp></paragraph>
  <bookmark branch="hid/SFX2_PUSHBUTTON_TP_HELP_INDEX_PB_OPEN_INDEX" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3150476"/><paragraph l10n="U" role="paragraph" id="par_id3148668" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="8"><ahelp hid="SFX2_PUSHBUTTON_TP_HELP_INDEX_PB_OPEN_INDEX" visibility="hidden">Click to display the selected topic.</ahelp></paragraph>
  <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="paragraph" id="par_id3155934" l10n="U" oldref="1">You can search for a specific topic by typing a word into the <emph>Search term</emph> text box. The window contains an alphabetical list of index terms.</paragraph>
  <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="paragraph" id="par_id3145669" l10n="U" oldref="6">If the cursor is in the index list when you type the search term, the display will jump directly to the next match. When you type a word in the <emph>Search term</emph> text box, the focus will jump to the best match in the index list.</paragraph>
  <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="tip" id="par_id3147653" l10n="U" oldref="7">The index and full-text searches always apply to the currently selected <item type="productname">%PRODUCTNAME</item> application. If the search is not successful, make sure the Help for the appropriate application is selected.</paragraph>
